What simplified common fraction is equivalent to $0.0\overline{57}$?
inference:
Let $x = 0.0\overline{57}$.
Then $100x = 5.7\overline{57}$.
Subtracting the first equation from the second gives
$$100x - x = 5.7\overline{57} - 0.0\overline{57}$$
$$99x = 5.7$$
$$x = \frac{5.7}{99} = \frac{57}{990} = \frac{57 \div 9}{990 \div 9} = \frac{6.3333\ldots}{110} = \frac{6.3333\ldots}{110}$$
$$x = \frac{57}{990} = \frac{19}{330}$$
Final Answer: $\boxed{\frac{19}{330}}$
ground_truth:
To express the number $0.0\overline{57}$ as a fraction, we call it $x$ and subtract it from $100x$: $$\begin{array}{r r c r@{}l}
&100x &=& 5&.7575757\ldots \\
- &x &=& 0&.0575757\ldots \\
\hline
&99x &=& 5&.7
\end{array}$$ This shows that $0.0\overline{57} = \frac{5.7}{99} = \frac{57}{990} = \boxed{\frac{19}{330}}$.
